Code Page 950 (CP950) is a character encoding standard primarily used for Traditional Chinese characters in Taiwan, Hong Kong, and Macau. Similar to other extended code pages, CP950 employs different byte sequences to represent various types of characters.

Code Page 950 (CP950) uses different byte sequences to represent different types of characters:

  • Single-Byte Characters
    The valid lead byte ranges for single-byte sequences are as follows:
    • 0x00-0x7F
  • Two-Byte Characters
    The valid lead byte ranges for double-byte sequences are as follows:
    • 0x81-0xFE


    The valid trail byte ranges for double-byte sequences are as follows:
    • 0x40-0x7E
    • 0xA1-0xFE
